<FIRST>r i PM-BRF--CrushedByElephant     10-30 0100</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Crushed By Elephant,0099</SECOND>
<HEAD>Pachyderm Kills Man For Beating Its Baby</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW DELHI, India (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An elephant trampled to death a man who
beat its baby for rampaging through his house in West Bengal state,
a news agency reported.
   A herd of 40 elephants arrived in the area last week and caused
havoc by trampling through houses and rice paddies, Press Trust of
India quoted police as saying. The death occurred at Salboni, about
60 miles west of Calcutta, Press Trust added in Monday's dispatch.
   The day of death and the sex of the elephant were not given.
