<FIRST>r a PM-WeatherpageWeather     10-30 0480</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0490</SECOND>
<HEAD>Indian Summer Continues in East; Rain, Clouds Across Midwest</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Indian summer was expected to linger for another day through
much of the East today, while a cold front stretching from Texas
north through the nation's midsection brings rain and perhaps some
snow.
   A high-wind warning was posted for this morning in Southern
California, where brushfires on Sunday chased 2,200 campers from
campgrounds in the mountains north of Los Angeles and closed a
stretch of the scenic Pacific Coast Highway near Malibu.
Firefighters were helped late Sunday by diminishing winds.
   New Englanders and New York state residents who have enjoyed
seven straight days of mild, sunny Indian summer weather were
advised to leave the overcoats home again today _ the forecast was
for clear skies and temperatures in the 60s and 70s.
   A mild, 70-degee day was in store for the mid-Atlantic states as
well, but forecasters warned clouds could creep in tonight. Rain
could reach New England from the north tonight or Tuesday, the
National Weather Service said.
   Meanwhile, a cold front stretching south from Wisconsin was
expected to bring cold rain to much of the Midwest today and
Tuesday. Snow flurries are possible in the upper Plains states.
   That follows a weekend bout of showers and storms that dumped
two-inch hail on some spots in Texas and Oklahoma and snow flurries
from South Dakota through southeast Colorado.
   Conditions at 3 a.m. EST:
   _EAST: Albany, N.Y., 42 foggy; Atlanta 60 fair; Boston 53 fair;
Charleston, S.C., 66 fair; Chattanooga 45 fair; Cincinnati 54 fair;
Cleveland 51 partly cloudy; Detroit 52 partly cloudy; Hatteras 70
cloudy; Jacksonville 69 windy; Key West 72 fair; Knoxville 45 fair;
Macon 60 fair; Miami 69 fair; New York 56 foggy; Philadelphia 50
foggy; Pittsburgh 50 foggy; Portland, Maine, 42 foggy; Richmond 58
foggy; Tampa 71 cloudy; Washington, D.C., 53 foggy.
   _CENTRAL: Birmingham 56 fair; Bismarck 22 fair; Chicago 57
partly cloudy; Denver 23 fair; Des Moines 48 cloudy; Indianapolis
50 fair; Kansas City 49 rain; Little Rock 53 fair; Louisville 49
fair; Memphis 57 partly cloudy; Nashville 50 fair; New Orleans 53
fair; North Platte 30 cloudy; Oklahoma City 54 thunderstorm; Omaha
45 windy; Rapid City 20 fair; St. Louis 63 cloudy; Minneapolis-St.
Paul 44 cloudy; Sault Ste. Marie 55 cloudy; San Antonio 71 cloudy.
   _WEST: Albuquerque 36 fair; Anchorage 28 foggy; Boise 32 cloudy;
Casper 14 fair; Fairbanks 14 cloudy; Great Falls 33 fair; Honolulu
72 partly cloudy; Las Vegas 46 fair; Los Angeles 64 partly cloudy;
Medford 33 fair; Pendleton 36 fair; Phoenix 61 fair; Portland,
Ore., 42 partly cloudy; Reno 27 fair; Salt Lake City 31 fair; San
