<HEAD>140 Fishermen Reported Missing in Storm</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DHAKA, Bangladesh (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   At least 140 fishermen are missing
after their motor boats capsized in a storm in the Bay of Bengal, a
newspaper reported Monday.
   The storm struck Oct. 19 off Chittagong, a port city 150 miles
southeast of Dhaka.
   Chittagong police said they had no figures but feared the
missing fishermen were dead, the Bangladesh Observer said.
   Fishing trawlers and other vessels have been asked to look for
survivors.
</TEXT>
