<HEAD>Two Die in Van-School Bus Accident</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PLYMOUTH, England (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A van and a school bus collided Monday
in southwestern England, killing two men in the van and injuring 56
students, police said.
   The girls, aged 9 to 18, were returning to their boarding school
in Torquay following the autumn half-term holiday.
   The injured were taken to Plymouth's Derriford Hospital and
Royal Naval Hospital.
   Police said they did not know what caused the accident.
</TEXT>
