<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Uganda-Attack     10-30 0110</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Uganda-Attack,0113</SECOND>
<HEAD>Gunmen Kill 7, Wound 13 at Weekend Party</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KAMPALA, Uganda (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Unidentified gunmen killed seven people
and wounded 13 in a weekend attack on revelers in northern Uganda,
a newspaper reported Monday.
   The attackers first demanded a cassette recorder playing music
at a Saturday night party called to celebrate a woman's graduation
from a police training school, the state-owned New Vision newspaper
reported.
   When refused the recorder, the gunmen threw a grenade into the
crowd and opened fire.
   The attack occurred near Kumi, 150 miles north of Kampala, an
area that is home to two rebel groups: the Holy Spirit Movement and
Uganda Peoples' Democratic Army.
</TEXT>
