<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Bangladesh-Clash     10-30 0116</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Bangladesh-Clash,0119</SECOND>
<HEAD>50 Injured in Student Clash at Khulna</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DHAKA, Bangladesh (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Moslem fundamentalist and secular
students battled each other with homemade bombs, pistols and iron
rods in Khulna, leaving at least 50 people injured, police said
Monday.
   The clash Sunday was precipitated by the campaign for the Nov. 4
student elections at Khulna College, police said by telephone in
the river port city 85 miles southwest of Dhaka.
   Two students were arrested and five others were hospitalized
with bullet wounds, the police said, speaking on condition of
anonymity.
   At least 10 people have been killed in clashes between
fundamentalist and secular students in the past six months at
universities and colleges around Bangladesh.
