<HEAD>Three Cabinet Members Leading Mission to Poland</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Three members of President Bush's Cabinet will
lead a delegation of government, business and labor officials to
Poland next month to assess what needs to be done to reform that
country's battered economy, the White House said today.
   The delegation will include Labor Secretary Elizabeth Dole,
