<FIRST>r i AM-Japan-Ship     10-30 0184</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Japan-Ship,0190</SECOND>
<HEAD>Nine Crew Missing after Ships Collide</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A South Korean chemical tanker and a
Panamanian-registered container vessel collided off southwestern
Japan early Tuesday and nine South Korean crew members are missing,
Japan's coast guard said.
   An official of the Maritime Safety Agency's office at Kochi said
an agency patrol boat rescued four crew drifting in a rubber boat,
but Capt. Kim Dong-an of the 755-ton Inchon Pioneer and eight
