   The Inchon Pioneer was bound from Yokohama to Oita, southwestern
Japan, with about 600 tons of alcohol-related products when the
collision with the Ever Guide occurred about 6 miles from Cape
Muroto, 390 miles southwest of Tokyo, the official said.
   He said the Ever Guide was sailing from Osaka to Taiwan.
   Six patrol boats and three aircraft are seaching for the missing
crew, he said.
