<FIRST>r f PM-VanFossan     10-30 0133</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Van Fossan,0138</SECOND>
<HEAD>CEO of The Mutual Benefit Life Insurance Dead at 63</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEWARK, N.J. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Robert V. Van Fossan, chairman and chief
executive officer of The Mutual Benefit Life Insurance Co., has
died at the age of 63, company officials said.
   Van Fossan, a resident of Mendham, died Sunday of cancer at
Morristown Memorial Hospital, the company said in a statement.
   Van Fossan joined Newark-based Mutual Benefit Life as president
and chief executive officer in 1972 at the age of 45, becoming the
youngest chief executive officer of any major American life
insurance company, company officials said.
   During his stewardship, the company grew nearly fivefold to its
current base of $11 billion and broadened its traditional life and
health insurance to include a wide range of financial products and
services.
</TEXT>
