<HEAD>London Shares Sharply Higher at Midday</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   London share prices rose sharply in extremely
light trading Monday, as the market benefited from a technical
rebound after its sharp fall on Friday, and responded to sterling's
healthy early tone.
   At about noon in London, the Financial Times-Stock Exchange
100-share index was up 28.2 points, or 1.3 percent, at 2,110.3
points, up from a morning low of 2,101.2 points.
   Despite the upturn, dealers said the market remained highly
nervous about a potential further weakening in sterling, which
might force Britain's new Chancellor of the Exchequer, John Major,
to hike interest rates.
   Volume came to an extremely light 129.9 million shares, compared
with 310.9 million shares at the same time Friday.
