<HEAD>Industry Reports Weekly Production</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHARLESTON, W.Va. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Domestic coal production totaled 19.3
million tons during the week ended Oct. 21, down 5 percent from the
20.4 million short tons produced in the previous week, the
Department of Energy reported Monday.
   The U.S. coal industry produced 18.9 million tons in the same
week last year, according to the department's Energy Information
Administration.
   Domestic coal production so far this year is 779.9 million tons,
5.8 percent above last year's production at this time, the agency
said.
   The week's production accounts for bituminous and lignite coal.
