<FIRST>r f BC-Earns-Unocal     10-30 0172</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Earns-Unocal,0177</SECOND>
<HEAD>Unocal Third-Quarter Earnings Fall 19 Percent</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Unocal Corp. said Monday its third-quarter
profits fell 19 percent due to escalating costs to produce oil and
gas and lower refining and marketing results.
   For the three-month third period, the Los Angeles-based oil, gas
and coal company earned $79 million, or 67 cents a share, down from
$97 million, or 84 cents a share, in the comparable 1988 quarter.
Revenue rose 8 percent to $2.8 billion from $2.6 billion.
   Unocal chairman Richard J. Stegemeier said the quarter's
negative results were partially offset by higher crude oil prices
and improved domestic natural gas production. A $6 million
after-tax gain from the sale of land in Canada, and a $14 million
reduction in deferred income taxes resulting from changes in the
company's state taxes also contributed.
   For the first nine months, Unocal's profits fell 16 percent to
$286 million, or $2.44 per share, from $339 million, or $2.91 a
share. Revenue rose 14 percent, to $8.5 billion from $7.5 billion.
</TEXT>
