<HEAD>Shoney's Restructuring to Trim Debt by $4 Million</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Shoney's Inc. aims to trim its debt by
$4 million in interest charges next year as part of its latest
restructuring in which it will refinance a $410 million debt.
   Shoney's, which has more than 1,500 restaurants nationwide,
borrowed $585 million in a restructuring last year.
   The refinancing reduces the interest on $160 million of the debt
to 9.78 percent from 11.66 percent, and reduces the overall
effective interest rate from 10.66 percent to 10.33 percent, the
company said.
   Also, 94 percent of the debt is now at fixed interest rates, up
from about 60 percent before the refinancing.
   Shoney's has repaid $175 million of the debt this year,
including $54 million in scheduled payments and $121 million in
pre-payments, according to Chief Financial Officer Taylor Henry Jr.
   The debt refinancing will require accelerated write-off for fees
related to the original financing, which will reduce fourth-quarter
earnings by 7 cents per share.
   Shoney's reports year-end earnings in mid-December. Revenues for
1989 are projected to be $45 million ahead of last year's figures,
Henry said.
</TEXT>
